{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.83",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 83,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 83 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:1",
      "text": "Keep not thou silence, O God: hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:2",
      "text": "For, lo, thine enemies make a tumult: and they that hate thee have lifted up the head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:3",
      "text": "They have taken crafty counsel against thy people, and consulted against thy hidden ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:4",
      "text": "They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from being a nation; that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:5",
      "text": "For they have consulted together with one consent: they are confederate against thee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:6",
      "text": "The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagarenes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:7",
      "text": "Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:8",
      "text": "Assur also is joined with them: they have holpen the children of Lot. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:9",
      "text": "Do unto them as unto the Midianites; as to Sisera, as to Jabin, at the brook of Kison:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:10",
      "text": "Which perished at En–dor: they became as dung for the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:11",
      "text": "Make their nobles like Oreb, and like Zeeb: yea, all their princes as Zebah, and as Zalmunna:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:12",
      "text": "Who said, Let us take to ourselves the houses of God in possession.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:13",
      "text": "O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:14",
      "text": "As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:15",
      "text": "So persecute them with thy tempest, and make them afraid with thy storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:16",
      "text": "Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek thy name, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:17",
      "text": "Let them be confounded and troubled for ever; yea, let them be put to shame, and perish:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.83.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:18",
      "text": "That men may know that thou, whose name alone is Jehovah, art the most high over all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
